'''Malakho''' is a recurring background character in the [[Season 2|second season]]. He is played by extra Robert &quot;Bebe&quot; Boroje and debuts in &quot;[[The North Remembers]].&quot; Malakho is an old [[Dothraki]] warrior in the [[khalasar]] of [[Daenerys Targaryen]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Malakho is an aged Dothraki in [[Khal]] [[Drogo]]'s ''[[khalasar]]''. After ''Ko'' [[Pono]] and ''Ko'' [[Jhaqo]] abandoned the ''khalasar'' following Drogo's incapacitation and death of Khal Drogo, Malakho remained. After Daenerys' hatched her three [[dragon]] eggs, Malakho pledged loyalty to the ''[[khaleesi]]''.

===[[Season 2]]===
Malakho can be seen in the background when Daenerys' silver horse dies of exhaustion in the [[Red Waste]],&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The North Remembers]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; and when the [[the Thirteen]] receive Daenerys at the gates of [[Qarth]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Garden of Bones]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Malakho attends the reception for Daenerys in the home of [[Xaro Xhoan Daxos]]. He and [[Kovarro]] have to be prevented from stealing Xaro's statuary.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Ghost of Harrenhal]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; He guards Daenerys during her return from a meeting with the [[Spice King]] and is present when she discovers the theft of her dragons.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Old Gods and the New]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; He guards Daenerys's room after the theft.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Man Without Honor]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

After the duplicity of Xaro Xhoan Daxos is discovered, Malakho is the one who forces the would-be [[King of Qarth]] into his empty vault.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Morghulis]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
